    dc:creator "Mikhaljova, Elena V." ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "The millipede family Diplomaragnidae Attems, 1907 in the Asian part of Russia with the descriptions of two new genera and seven new species (Diplopoda, Chordeumatida)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606673>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606693>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606687>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606675>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606681>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606685>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606677>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606713>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606697>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606709> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606673>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–2. Alineuma rodionovi sp. nov., male holotype. 1, gonopods, front view; 2, gonopods, caudal view, right femur of posterior gonopod telopodite is twisted; ms, trapezoidal structure; b, hyaline fimbriate branch; ap, anterior angiocoxal process; pp, posterior angiocoxal process; at, anterior gonopod telopodite; sg, subglobule of posterior angiocoxite. Scale in mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606673/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606693>
    dc:description "FIGURES 28–31. Orientyla dahurica (Gerstfeldt, 1859), male. 28, gonopods, caudal view; 29, gonopods, front view; 30, distal parts of colpocoxites, front view; 31, apex of colpocoxite, front view; lp, lateral process of sheath groove; at, anterior gonopod telopodite; e, edge of sheath groove; pp, posterior angicoxal process; cx, coxosternum. Scales: 20 μm (Fig. 31), 100 μm (Fig. 29), 200 μm (Fig. 28), 0.5 mm (Fig. 30)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606693/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606687>
    dc:description "FIGURES 17–22. Litovkia anisimovka sp. nov., male paratype. 17, distal part of leg 4; 18, leg 4 without coxa and trochanter; 19, leg pair 11, caudal view; 20, coxae and trochanters 11, caudal view; 21, gonopods, caudal view, telopodites of posterior gonopods broken; 22, distal part of gonopods, caudal view; r, ridges-filaments; pp, posterior angicoxal process; ap, bifid anterior angiocoxal process; at, anterior gonopod telopodite; a, glabrous area. Scales: 20 μm (Figs 17, 22), 100 μm (Figs 18–21)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606687/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606675>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3–7. Diplomaragna budilovi sp. nov., male holotype. 3, 7, gonopods, caudal view; 4, posterior angiocoxal processes and colpocoxites, caudal view; 5, gonopods, front view; 6, basal part of gonopods, caudal view; c, horn; pp, posterior angicoxal process; ap, anterior angiocoxal process; cx, coxosternum; at, anterior gonopod telopodite. Scales: 20 μm (Fig. 6), 100 μm (Figs 3–5), 0.5 mm (Fig. 7)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606675/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606681>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13–14. Diplomaragna provecta Mikhaljova, 2005, male. 13, gonopods, caudal view; 14, central part of colpocoxite; pp, posterior angicoxal process; pt, posterior gonopod telopodite; cl, colpocoxites. Scales: 20 μm (Fig. 14), 100 μm (Fig. 13)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606681/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606685>
    dc:description "FIGURES 15–16. Diplomaragna yakovlevka Shear, 1990, male. 15, gonopods, caudal view; 16, posterior angiocoxal processes, caudal view; sg, subglobule of posterior angiocoxite. Scales: 20 μm (Fig. 16), 100 μm (Fig. 15)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606685/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606677>
    dc:description "FIGURES 8–12. Diplomaragna dentifer sp. nov., male, female paratypes. 8, gonopods, caudal view; 9, 10, posterior angiocoxal processes; 11, gonopods, front view; 12, vulvae, ventral view; pp, posterior angicoxal process; t, process-tooth; ap, anterior angiocoxal process. Scales: 20 μm (Figs 9–10), 100 μm (Figs 8, 11–12)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606677/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606713>
    dc:description "FIGURES 56–57. Pacifiosoma triangulatum sp. nov., male holotype. 56, gonopods, caudal view; 57, gonopods, front view; pp, posterior angicoxal process; c, clawlike outgrowth; n, triangular plate; ap, anterior angiocoxal process; cx, coxosternum. Scale in mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606713/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606697>
    dc:description "FIGURES 32–36. Pacifiosoma acutum sp. nov., male holotype. 32, 36, gonopods, caudal view, right colpocoxite broken; 33, posterior angiocoxal processes; 34, distal parts of anterior gonopod telopodite and colpocoxite; 35, external edge of colpocoxite; pp, posterior angicoxal process; n, external edge of colpocoxite; at, anterior gonopod telopodite; c, clawlike outgrowth. Scales: 10 μm (Figs 34–35), 20 μm (Fig. 33), 100 μm (Fig. 32), 0.5 mm (Fig. 36)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606697/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5606709>
    dc:description "FIGURES 45–48. Pacifiosoma cristofer (Mikhaljova, 1993), males from Gassi Lake basin (Figs 45–46) and Bolshekhekhtsirsky Nature Reserve (Figs 47–48). 45, 47, gonopods, front view; 46, 48, distal parts of colpocoxites; ap, anterior angiocoxal process; cl, colpocoxites. Scales: 20 μm (Figs 46, 48), 100 μm (Figs 45, 47)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5606709/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

